questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application's transactional integrity is compromised. The following service is used to book seats and log failures to an audit table:

java
@Service
public class BookingService {
    @Transactional
    public void bookSeat(String seatId) {
        try {
            reserveInventory(seatId);
        } catch (InventoryException e) {
            logFailureToAuditDb(seatId, e.getMessage());
            throw e;
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void logFailureToAuditDb(String seatId, String reason) {
        // Inserts into AUDIT_LOG table
    }
}


When `reserveInventory` throws an `InventoryException`, the transaction rolls back, but surprisingly, no entry is found in the `AUDIT_LOG` table, even though `logFailureToAuditDb` is annotated with `Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW`.
